      • getTagsWhichContainCommit

        public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> getTagsWhichContainCommit(java.lang.String gitCommitId)
        Gets the earliest commit that contains the commit.

        Uses the git tag --contains command to get all tags that contains the given gitCommitId.

        Note: returned tags are not ordered.

        Note: the JGit library does not support the git-describe command yet, hence the use of the command line.

        Specified by:
        getTagsWhichContainCommit in interface GitRepositoryClient
        See Also:
        GitClientSupport.tagContains(java.io.File, String)
